  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN144.1-kilavi">viṉaimuṟṟiya talaimakaṉ <app><lem>pākaṟkuc</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C5v #C9">pākaṟkuc taṉ neñiṟkuc</rdg><rdg wit="#C7 #RK">taṉṉeñiṟkuraippāṉāy pākaṟkuc</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE who had finished [his] work said to the charioteer. </p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN144.1">
              <l>varutu meṉṟa nāḷum poyttaṉa</l>
              <l>variyē yuṇka ṇīru nillā</l>
              <l>taṇkārk kīṉṟa paiṅkoṭi mullai</l>
              <l>vaivāy vā<supplied>ṉ</supplied>mukai yaviḻnta kōtai</l>
              <l>peyvaṉap pi<supplied>ḻa</supplied>nta katuppu muḷḷā</l>
              <l>raruḷakaṉ māṟalō māṟuka vanti</l>
              <l>laṟaṉañ calarē yāyiḻai namareṉac</l>
              <l>ciṟiyac collip periya pu<supplied>la</supplied>ppiṉum</l>
              <l>paṉipaṭu naṟuntār kuḻaiya nammoṭu</l>
              <l>tuṉitīr muyakkam peṟṟōḷ pōla</l>
              <l>vuvakkuvaḷ vāḻiya neñcē vicumpi</l>
              <l><supplied>ṉē</supplied>ṟeḻuntu mu<supplied>ḻa</supplied>ṅkiṉu māṟeḻuntu cilaikkuṅ</l>
              <l>kaṭāa yāṉai koṭkum pā<supplied>ca</supplied>ṟaip</l>
              <l>pōrvēṭ ṭeḻunta maḷḷar kai<supplied>ya</supplied>tai</l>
              <l>kūrvāṭ kuvi<del>mu</del>mukañ citaiya nūṟi</l>
              <l>māṉaṭi maruṅkiṟ peyartta kuruti</l>
              <l>vāṉa mīṉiṉ vayiṉvayi ṉimaippa</l>
              <l>vamarōrt taṭṭa celvan</l>
              <l>tamarvirain turaippak kēṭku ñāṉṟē</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>“All the days, of which he said “we will come”, have turned false. (1)</l>
                <l>The water does not stop in [my] kajal eyes with red streaks, (2)</l>
                <l>and he does not remember [my] hair that has lost [its] beauty, wearing (5)</l>
                <l>a wreath on which have opened the sharp-mouthed pure buds (4)</l>
                <l>of the jasmine in fresh creepers that were brought forth by the cool rainy season, (3)</l>
                <l>A change in [his] consideration, ah, may it come about. There (6)</l>
                <l>he is fearless in [his] duty, our man with choice jewels ” – (7)</l>
                <l>even if she is greatly vexed, speaking little [complaints like that], (8)</l>
                <l>she will rejoice, (11a)</l>
                <l>as if she had [already] obtained a depression-ending embrace (10)</l>
                <l>from us, so that [her] bedewed fragrant garland is spoiled, (9)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">may you live, heart, (11 bc)</l>
                <l>– at the time [she] hears their people hurriedly talk about (19)</l>
                <l>the wealth that was killed, regarding the war, (18)</l>
                <l>when on every side the [drops] of blood that gathered</l>
                <l>in the foot [prints] of the [war] animals, twinkled like stars in the sky, (16f.)</l>
                <l>as warriors who had risen desirous of battle demolished [the sword] in the hand</l>
                <l>so that the piled edges of sharp swords were ruined, (14f.)</l>
                <l>in the war camp where rutting elephants roam, (12)</l>
                <l>when [thunder] strokes rise in the sky [and] the change [of weather] resounds [louder] than a drum. (10df.)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
